Package model

package model
  • Class
    Description
    Admin
    Represents an Admin in the HMS system, inheriting from the HMSPersonnel class.
    AppointmentOutcomeRecord
    Represents the outcome record of a patient's appointment.
    AppointmentRecord
    Represents an appointment record, containing patient details, appointment time, status, location, and associated appointment outcome.
    Diagnosis
    Represents a Diagnosis made for a patient, which includes details such as the diagnosis description, treatment plans, prescriptions, and relevant IDs for patient, doctor, and medical records.
    Doctor
    Represents a Doctor in the system.
    HMSPersonnel
    Represents a personnel in the Hospital Management System (HMS).
    HMSRecords
    Abstract class representing a generic record in the Hospital Management System (HMS).
    MedicalHistory
    Represents the medical history of a patient, containing a list of medical records and the associated patient.
    MedicalRecord
    Represents a medical record for a patient, containing personal information, blood type, allergies, and a list of diagnoses.
    Medicine
    Represents a medicine in the system.
    Patient
    Represents a patient in the healthcare management system, including personal information, insurance details, allergies, and date of admission.
    PaymentRecord
    Represents a payment record in the system.
    Pharmacist
    Represents a pharmacist in the system, extending the HMSPersonnel class to include specific details such as the pharmacist's license number and date of employment.
    PrescribedMedication
    Represents a prescribed medication for a patient, including information about the diagnosis, medicine, dosage, and treatment duration.
    Prescription
    Represents a prescription for a patient, including the diagnosis ID, prescription date, and the medications prescribed as part of the treatment.
    RecordStatusType
    Enum representing the different statuses of a record.
    SessionCookie
    Represents a session cookie for a user in the system.
    TreatmentPlans
    Represents a Treatment Plan associated with a particular diagnosis.
